<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1918-03-30T18:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1918-03-30T18:00:00-05:00" n="743" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d743">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 763.72/9405a</note>
                            <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of
                                        State</gloss> to the Consul at Tiflis</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_SFW1" type="to"><hi rend="italic">Smith</hi></persName>)<note n="1" xml:id="d743fn1">Sent via the
                                    Legation in Persia (No. 37).</note></head>
                            <opener>
                                <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                            </opener>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1918-03-30T18:00:00-05:00"><hi rend="italic">March 30,
                                            1918, 6 p.m.</hi></date></dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>Referring your recent telegrams March 10 to 15.<note n="2" xml:id="d743fn2">Not printed; see telegram to the Ambassador in
                                    Great Britain (No. 7116), Apr. 3, <hi rend="italic">infra</hi>.</note> The United States is not in a position to
                                support active military operations on Caucasus front. Summary of
                                your reports has been communicated to British Government. Messages
                                to Barton<note n="3" xml:id="d743fn3">The Rev. Dr. <persName>James
                                        L. Barton</persName>, foreign secretary of the American
                                    Board of Commissioners for Foreign Missions.</note> and Red
                                Cross also delivered. Department will advise whether any measures
                                possible to relieve situation among civilian population.</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed><persName corresp="#p_LR1"><hi rend="smallcaps">Lansing</hi></persName></signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>